            <p:rationale>Organizational boundaries have begun to fade as employees increasingly work from different locations. In addition, external parties require increased access to applications, and firewalls provide only limited protection filtering through-traffic. By securing data close to the source, confidentiality is guaranteed independent of the various access paths.</p:rationale>
            <p:implications>Network traffic is filtered on entry into the data center and monitored for hostility. Confidential data is encrypted within application content. Passwords are transported in a non-readable form on the network. Applications always perform an authentication and authorization of users or systems that want to access functionality or data.</p:implications>
